What you need to know:

President Uhuru Kenyatta, when he was the minister for Local Government in 2008, tried in vain to decongest the city centre by banning all buses and matatus from its streets.Former Nairobi Governor Dr Evans Kidero formed a task force incorporating different stakeholders in the transport sector in 2015.In December 2018, incumbent governor Mike Sonko revisited the matter, more determined to get it right.